Title: Enabling Production Studies and Concepts                                                                                             -             -       24.437
Description: The Enabling Production Studies and Concepts thrust is developing technologies that enable the production of
molecules, materials, and parts in an expeditionary setting that will untether military forces from supply chains and enable a
continuous global presence. Focus areas include making products at the point of need from local feedstock, developing the
ability to use non-optimized materials in manufacturing; accelerating part qualification; and new approaches to developing room
temperature superconductors and efficient thermoelectric materials.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded as Making and Maintaining in Materials Processing Technologies in PE 0602715E,
Project MBT-01.

