toughness.
- Assess ceramic microstructure stability through elevated temperature exposure.
- Explore novel chemical structures that enable the controlled reaction of energetic materials.
- Research and design use of Lithium slurries with seawater as fuel in uncrewed underwater vehicles to extend deployment range
and endurance.
- Explore novel approaches, including emerging interlocking metasurfaces, to decrease maintenance time and allow for mission-
specific reconfigurability.
- Explore concepts to engage manufacturing workforce to close projected gap.
- Explore tunable surfaces to reflect and change both spatial and frequency aspects of signals for successful blue comms and
unsuccessful red.
- Evaluate potential for separation of rare earth elements from each other using excited electronic state features.
- Begin development of a new mathematical framework to dynamically create and leverage multiple degrees of freedom.
- Begin designing a mixed signal National Imagery Interpretability Rating Scale (NIIRS) for efficiency and effectiveness.
- Conduct exploratory research to develop polymers that could self-heal undersea infrastructure such as pipelines.
- Investigate the feasibility of exploiting nanofluidic phenomena to dramatically increase efficiency of multistep complex chemical
synthesis.

