Title: Complex Modeling Studies and Concepts                                                                                                -             -       15.237
Description: The Complex Modeling Studies and Analysis thrust is exploring novel approaches to modeling and controlling
physical environments in various conditions for improved platform design. Nonlinear flow conditions represent some of the oldest
unsolved challenges in physics. The ability to model high-Reynolds number classical turbulence, for instance, or turbulent
cascades in compressible fluids, is extremely limited. Focus areas include new modeling and simulation tools to understand
complex physical conditions, and to aid engineers in design, regardless of scale.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded as Access in Materials Processing Technology in Technology in PE 0602715E, Project
MBT-01.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Assess feasibility of re-purposing hot, high-density plasma used in fusion experiments for electric propulsion applications.
