Title: Willow                                                                                                                                 -             -       24.000
Description: The Willow program will develop innovative payloads to conduct Acoustic Warfare (AW) to counter active surface
sonars using a unique combination of acoustic hardware and waveforms provided by advanced sonar signal processing
algorithms. Willow will provide a robust capability to help the Navy respond to active sonar threats. No current method exists
to challenge adversary active sonars. Willow will use advanced hardware-in-the-loop simulations, Independent Verification and
Validation (IV&V), and stressing at-sea testing to create this capability. Technology developed under this program will transition to
the Navy.

Prior to FY 2026, this program was funded in PE 0603766E, Project NET-02.


