N/A
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY26 Increase due to increased focus on potential Fleet risk due to unsupported platforms. Reverse Engineering
plans have been re-implemented for FY26 and will be used to mitigate that risk.
Title: Clothing Protection for the Warfighter                                                                            0.425      0.630       0.505      0.000       0.505
                                                                                                         Articles:          -          -           -          -           -
Description: Identify challenges to effectively manage durability and safety aspects of common work/combat
uniforms for the warfighter. Eliminate risk of hazardous factors such as fire, weather, and general wear/tear to
maximize readiness and strength in Fleet uniforms. Assist with specifications associated with permanent press
finish related to the rollout of the Navy's Type III uniform.

FY 2025 Plans:
Assessment of the Effect of Women Specific Sizing on Clothing System Performance ($155K): Most Navy
organizational and protective clothing and individual equipment items lack women specific sizes. Garment
and equipment fit impact Sailors' maneuverability and comfort and the clothing system's thermoregulatory and
protective performance. This effort would assess the impact of women specific sized garments, handwear, and
footwear, as compared to unisex/men's sized items, on the biophysical performance and protective performance
using SHEMO thermal manikin and female flame manikin, respectively.




