FY 2026 Plans:
Efforts in support of Disruptive Technology include but not limited to:
- Conduct Demonstrations and assessments of multi-mission and Multi-domain missile defense technologies to transition to
programs of record.
- Invest in Key technologies to enable Over the Horizon Kill Chains and disruptive adversary kill chains.
- Invest in enabling technologies to include:
-- Leveraging Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning for more effective missile defense system performance.
-- Further investments in the development, assessment, and processing techniques of advanced materials for missiles, sensors,
and command and control components.
-- Additive manufacturing.
- Develop radiation hardened components to enable high volume of on-orbit data processing.
- Broaden the use and applicability of Electronic Warfare technologies to include High Power Microwave, traditional Radar and
radio frequency sensor systems as well as nearfield effects, cyber physical, and space domain for future Missile Defense System
concepts.
- Increase technology maturation levels and develop prototypes to support near term capabilities for the warfighter.
- Initiate Multi-Sensor Capability technologies (Ground-Air-Space) and fundamental future effector technologies (space based,
propulsion, non-kinetic).
- Integrate digital technology into existing processes, products, and emerging technologies to enable continual, rapid, delivery-
driven capability to the warfighter.
