FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase from FY 2025 to FY 2026 provides for the development and acceleration of critical capabilities against advanced
threats in the terminal phase of flight including ballistic, hypersonic, cruise, and other advanced ballistic and non-ballistic missile
threats. These critical capabilities, such as Dynamic Deployment of the Interceptor's Aft Flare (Q-Flare), adjustments to the Radar
constraints, and Relaxed Battlespace Optimization, increase both the defended and launch areas of the THAAD weapon system.
Enhancing the tracking and discrimination algorithms in the Fire Control and AN/TPY-2 radar will improve the effectiveness and
performance of the system. Additionally, the budget increase supports the integration of the THAAD weapon system into the
Army's IBCS architecture. Lastly, the budget increase enables significant system improvements to modernize the software base
and incorporate lessons learned from recent, real-world events into focused THAAD improvements to defeat new, advanced
threat systems and improve life-cycle sustainment.
