capability with the ACB 20 Combat System, to include new AN/SPY-6 requirements. Aegis BMD 6.0.1 exploits AN/SPY-6 radar
improvements to enhance Search, Track and Engagement capabilities, to include discrimination, raid defense and expanded
threat space. This improved performance will enable Missile Defense System element utilization of AN/SPY-6(V)1 data for remote
engagements and will supplement deployed assets with simultaneous multi-mission capabilities (e.g., IAMD). AMDR will support
a force-level (multi-asset) approach to raid defense and will enable U.S. Navy ships to have a greater stand-off range from threat
environments.
